main event: A series of sightings of unidentified flying objects were reported in Alabama, Arkansas, Ohio, and Louisiana in September 1966.
interesting points: The sightings involved bright, glowing objects in the night sky, some resembling comets or celestial phenomena.
One object was described as a 'Martian cloud' released by a four-stage Javelin rocket launched from Wallops Island, Virginia on September 24, 1966.
Another object was estimated to be 150 to 300 feet in length, bright reddish-orange in color, and left a trail of reddish-orange sparks.
The objects were observed traversing the sky from southwest to northeast, and some were visible for several minutes.
The report includes photographs of the various unidentified objects and phenomena observed during these sightings.
